  <div class="comment__text-wrapper">
    <footer class="comment__meta">
      <p class="comment__author"><span>Lori (not verified)</span></p>
      <p class="comment__time">5 years ago</p>
                </footer>
    <div class="comment__content">
      
            <div class="text-content field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item comment__text-content"><p>I bought transplant lettuce at the grocery store (established plants, ready to plant). They did well after I planted them in the planters, and doubled their growth. So, I decided to harvest it. But, I cut almost all of the leaves, including the ones in the center. Did I kill my lettuce plants or will they regrow? We live in an area in Europe where the weather is between 40’s, for lows, and 50’s for highs all day....Thank you for your insight!</p>
</div>
      <ul class="links inline comment__links">
          <li class="comment__links-item"><a href="/comment/reply/node/90183/comment_node_plant/110020" class="comment__links-link">Reply</a></li>
