<div class="indented">
<article  data-comment-user-id="343787" id="comment-110099" class="comment" role="article" data-drupal-selector="comment">
  <div class="comment__text-wrapper">
    <footer class="comment__meta">
      <p class="comment__author"><a title="View user profile." href="/author/editors">The Editors</a></p>
      <p class="comment__time">4 years 12 months ago</p>
                    <p class="visually-hidden">In reply to <a href="/comment/110020#comment-110020" class="permalink" rel="bookmark" hreflang="und">Did I Kill My Lettuce Plants?</a> by <span>Lori (not verified)</span></p>
          </footer>
    <div class="comment__content">
      
            <div class="text-content field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item comment__text-content"><p>It depends how you harvested. If you cut off all the leaves with scissor at soil level, it will grow back in a few weeks. You may even get a third cutting. This “cut and come again” method is actually our preferred way to go. Obviously, if you pulled the whole head or any of the roots, that&#8217;s it! Seed more&nbsp;lettuce.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
      <ul class="links inline comment__links">
          <li class="comment__links-item"><a href="/comment/reply/node/90183/comment_node_plant/110099" class="comment__links-link">Reply</a></li>
